The kernel type-checker (src-java/ansatz/kernel/TypeChecker.java and
related files under src-java/ansatz/kernel/) is a reimplementation of
the Lean 4 kernel type-checker algorithm:

  Lean 4 (https://github.com/leanprover/lean4)
  Copyright (c) 2013-2014 Microsoft Corporation
  Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0

The original Lean 4 kernel was authored by Leonardo de Moura.
The reimplementation is in Java and follows the same type-theoretic
algorithm (definitional equality, lazy delta reduction, universe
polymorphism) as described in the Lean 4 source and the underlying
dependent type theory literature.
